    "However, when a microlensing HME takes place there is much more information to be extracted on the immediate vicinity of the SMBH, e.g.",
    "its event horizon, mass, and spin.",
    "The magnification during such events can often be described analytically, which can make modelling simpler (see also Sect. 3.5.6).",
    "Mediavilla et al. (2015) use three such events in Q 2237+0305 whose fine structure at the peak they attribute to the Innermost Stable Circular Orbit (ISCO) at ≈ 3 gravitational radii.",
